CGTN's Music Voyage launched a brand-new Winter Olympics Special on Saturday, bringing together musicians from home and abroad to produce a musical composition under the Beijing 2022 theme of "Together, for a shared future."Â The four musicians of different cultural backgrounds are required to produce a minute each of the composition based on their own music styles and their understanding of winter sports and Beijing 2022 within seven days in a relay format. The end result will be an exclusive Olympic theme tune for CGTN. Who are the producers? Asr: Keyboardist Born in 1990, Asr is an ethnic Mongolian from north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region. He plays Matouqin, or the morin khuur and horsehead fiddle, a traditional Mongolian bowed stringed instrument. Mico: Drummer This electronic music producer, drummer, DJ and traveler has performed in 35 countries and regions. The talented artist leads the JungleMico Project band and has been featured on the front page of the U.S. music blog Electro Wow. Doctor Victor: DJ Doctor Victor is a full-time physician in Iceland, but also performs as a professional musician and DJ. He played music at vaccination sites at the height of the COVID-19 pandemic in Iceland to soothe people's fears. Carlo Facchini: Composer Italian music master, Carlo Facchini, led a popular rock n roll band when he was young. He is now looking forward to adding finishing touches of classical and romantic Italian music to the CGTN Winter Olympic theme tune. Please stay tuned to CGTN to discover how the musicians conquer the challenges and cross-cultural barriers in the next few weeks, as they showcase their passion, pleasure and hard work in creating theme music for a special occasion.